We recommended that the LCE to undertake the following courses of action:

instruct the Budget Officer to explain why the COVID-19 HP was paid using the appropriation intended for payment of salaries, wages, GSIS Life and Retirement, HP, and MOOE without a corresponding SB Resolutions/Realignment of Funds;

instruct the HRMO to (i) submit the DTRs or any other means of recording attendance; order authorizing the employees to physically report for work; copy of the duties and responsibilities of Casual and Job Order personnel during the period of grant; and require the person responsible to submit the minutes of sessions and/or entries of attendance in the logbook during the implementation of ECQ to substantiate COVID-19 HP given to the barangay officials and (ii) scrutinize the submitted DTRs especially the time in and out to arrive at the correct man-hour/attendance actually rendered to avoid overpayment or underpayment of claims;

advise the OIC-Municipal Accountant to verify and cross-check all data relating to payroll of employees with the approved DTRs and accomplishment reports; and

direct the head of each department having jurisdiction of the subject employees to ensure the correctness of information disclosed in the DTRs and accomplishment reports before approving the same.

We recommended that the LCE, being the Chairman of the GFPS, through its Focal Person undertake the following courses of action:

exhaust all available resources for the collection and processing of data requirements for GAD database;

prioritize measures on the development and updating of the GAD Code to provide authority on management actions and decisions;

revisit the GAD Plan and determine the reasons and factors contributing to the non-implementation of GAD PPAs.  Exert effort to pursue all planned PPAs considering their sensitivity to gender and existing need based on sex-disaggregated data;

advice the Monitoring and Evaluation Team to take responsibility of assessing the status of PPAs in relation to the plan and existing GAD policy; and

ensure that GAD Accomplishment Report is supported with (i) copies of reported policy issuances; and (ii) results of Harmonized Gender and Development Guidelines (HGDG) tests to provide basis of measuring the performance of the LGU.

